Features:
-Windows 8.1 Update 1 17025 build (wzt msu leak)
-Non-Activated and KMS-Activated indexes. Take your pick.*
*Uses AutoKMS folder in Windows directory. I've included the task
removal script if you wish to remove the AutoKMS task and/or files.
-Highly Compressed install.esd recovery compression format.
-DaRT 8.1 integrated into boot.wim recovery options. Choose Repair
your computer, Troubleshoot, then MS DaRT options to open. Features
include an offline defender a/v scanner, password reset tool, registry
editor, offline hotfix removal, system file checker, and many more.
-UEFI boot information added to ISO boot data

Notes:
-Update1 build 17025 was added without using resetbase to allow future
removal if it blocks a newer version from being installed such that
the previous version did. Actual file version numbers will vary.
-This version uses AutoKMS from Microsoft Toolkit 2.5 (CODYQX4)*
*AutoKMS will re-activate your system every 24 hours or every time you
reboot. Every time it is ran, it will re-schedule itself.
-The non-activated index is meant for people who wish to use a different
kms activation method. This entire release is not meant for retail
activation, though you can easily restore a retail ProWMC key by
copying over data.dat and tokens.dat and setting the pkey with slmgr.
